Here is the summarized list of commands for your reference:

# Navigate to project directory
cd path/to/your/project

# Build and start the containers
docker compose up --build

# Verify the containers are running
docker ps

# Access the application at http://localhost:3000

# View logs (optional)
docker compose logs -f

# Stop the containers
docker compose down

By following these steps, you should be able to run both your PostgreSQL database container and your NestJS application container seamlessly.
